I love the idea that this app will help because gluten takes forms in many ingredients and it‚Äôs hard to remember each ingredient or have to search it up while food shopping. However, upon installing the app it‚Äôs been giving me a hard time setting up an account and loading each screen on the app! Navigating through each screen and on each page the app is malfunctioning and there‚Äôs a pop up saying ‚ÄúError! Something went wrong‚Äù ... what is this madness?! I have deleted the app, restarted my phone and reinstalled, still nothing. It‚Äôs being downloaded over strong WiFi, so I know connection isn‚Äôt the issue. However this is very disappointing to the point that I had to write a review and let the developers know there is a serious bug and it needs to be fixed, my review won‚Äôt be changed until then, when I can get the full experience of the app.
response: Hi Jasmine, we would love to help you on your gluten free journey. We found and fixed the issue you are referring to. Please try once more. If you need additional support, we can help at support@innit.com

For example, I searched ‚Äúcondensed soup‚Äù and only got a handful of results when I know there are many, many soups logged on the app. It would be nice to have more results and maybe even a way to filter them in the future.

As an example I‚Äôll use the terms disaccharides and sulfites from the app. Let‚Äôs say a new user sees these terms and doesn't know what they are. It would be really cool if there was a way for its information to be displayed through a double click or if it was just there. I hope I came up with something useful.

title: Life Saver!!

title: Extremely useful
body: I disagree with what some reviewers are saying about this app being misleading.  It is accurate in telling you what you should avoid according to YOUR preferences you input. While there may be some things on here that will score ok that you wouldn't eat because of GMO's or additives and things like that. But if you are a super naturalist you don't need an app to know that the most "clean" foods are organically grown produce from local farms and non caged and well fed animals for meats. HOWEVER this app is used for scanning PACKAGED foods!! And the reality is, although we are more health conscious than ever, most companies can't keep up with demand w/o some unfavorable preservative ect. So that being said, I've found this app extremely useful!! The scanning feature easy and fun. It's helped me stay away from gluten and from there you can determine if something they suggest is ok for you particularly. Totally worth it app. I've never used a nutrition/food shopping app more. :)

title: Perfect!
body: This app is perfect. Not only is it specifically designed for those with food allergies (nuts, dairy, wheat, gluten, etc.) you can customize it to let it tell you what to avoid based on your specific diet needs. So, if you want to avoid foods with high fructose corn syrup, or eat foods high in protein, or avoid foods low in saturated fat, anything specific, then this app does that too! The scanner is fast and accurate, letting you know to "avoid" it and why or letting you know if the food is good for you based on your diet/allergies. It will even rate the food for you on a percentage scale and gives you better suggestions to increase what it is you want to intake more of!

title: Great app- could use added features
body: I just started using this app and quite like it so far. The break down of what is good vs bad in the nutrition and ingredient lists is fantastic and I enjoy knowing why a food is rated with it's particular score. I think the app could use a little more personalization in the profile set-up. When determining what's right for you it should take into account your true age (not a 31 year gap- since being a 22 year old is certainly different than 44). It would also be useful if it took in a persons weight, height and body type; all these things can influence what is better or worse for your diet. A food diary that notes needed calories and nurtritional needs with daily intake would be nice too. It would be great to see this app take things just one step further- then it would be worth 5 stars.

title: Has really opened my kids eyes
body: I really like this and it has been helpful with my kids making better choices.  We probably scan everything to see what score comes up or to see how much healthier it is. My kids don't want to touch anything with a scale lower than 60 (not sure why, probably because of the grading scale).  However, I have been surprised how much healthier some kids cereals were over "healthy" brands and I have rethought some of my own choices.  I would give it 5 Stars, but I am not sure how to add a product and suggested alternates were little off (scanned diced tomatoes and alternatives were tomato paste).  There were options for things to like and don't like, but I really don't know what they were there for.  Also I wish I could my own products on the shopping list.

title: Awesome decoding food app!!
body: Love that this app is able to let you know if a product has harmful preservatives without you needing a degree in nutritional science to figure it out.   Also, it gives you examples of every type of food that you could think of that would best match your health requirements or simply scan an item's barcode to find out, so convenient.  Another great idea was the coloring/numbering system that tells you where a particular food weighs in, in terms of whether or not it is the right food choice for you.  So whatever your diet situation needs are like avoiding foods with certain allergens, avoiding foods because of high blood pressure or certain diseases, or just to be health conscious and savvy to maintain general health this is a really great tool for all these.

title: Love this app
body: I have been looking for something like this for a while now! It makes it easy to figure out what to buy at the store, and I found that some of the stuff I was buying wasn't as healthy as I thought. I also discovered some stuff was actually better than I thought! It's great when confronted by so many different brands of the same item, and now I can choose the healthiest choice. I wish it had more store brand items available such as Kroger and Hy-Vee store brands, but I can compare their nutrition info to the name brands. I can vouch that it DOES NOT promote the major brands like the first review states. If your "health" food doesn't rate very high, it's probably because it isn't actually that healthy.

title: Could stand a few changes
body: It's a useful app for the most part. It's easier to read the ingredient list on it than on some packaging - provided the product is in the database. The first improvement needed is the ability to add your personal food allergies. In my case it would be grapes, cilantro, bell peppers, and broccoli. I became extremely sick a few weeks back because I didn't realize I had accidentally grabbed something with grape juice in it. The other thing that needs to be tweaked is the fact that the app will flagged added sugar products, even if you don't select that as something you want to avoid. If it's going to flag the substance anyway, there's no point of pretending we have a choice in the matter. I know that processed sugar is not the best of substances, but it's better than digestive problems I get from grapes and artificial sweeteners. Frankly, it would help me more if the app differentiated between raw sugar, brown sugar, and white sugar.

title: Great App for food searching!
body: This app lets you search for food and look at the nutrition, ingredients, and benefits it will have or not have for you, based on a personal profile that you create about yourself. You pick what you want in food (protein, calcium, low fat, etc.) and what you don't want (sugar, sat. fat, sodium, etc), so can find out if that food you're looking for is healthy or not, and if it isn't then there are healthier alternatives available for you to look at and learn about. This is a great app for shopping, learning. It helps teach you more about what's in the food you eat. I recommend this app, I use it when I'm curious about buying food, whether it's candy or a type of yogurt.

title: SheRambo
body: I Absolutely love this app...

title: Food-sensational!
body: Any app that makes life simple by means of removing stress from our lives to allow us to spend more time on what makes us not only happy but healthy is exceptional and a must have app.  This food app allows you tailor your nutritional needs, provides great quick info and a graded score to quickly let you know if an item is a go or no good.  Plus it provides badges for accomplishments who doesn't love rewards. Speaking of rewards, this app offers missions which will potentially offer such items as gift cards.  Aside from these fun highlights, the app offers a wide array of many useful features and benefits that you just have to down load and explore for yourself.

title: Great App, It Helps Me a Lot
body: I've been using this app for about a month now and I have to say it's one the few apps I use at least three times a week. It's helped me to choose better quality items and avoid items I didn't realize had ingredients that were undermining my goals; and I've been reading the nutritional labels closely. There are a couple things I'd like to see improved. One, a larger database but this app is still pretty new and I know the nutritionists making sure the data that is in the database is correct. Two, and I know this is asking a lot, but if this some how could sync with some of the fitness and health monitoring apps that would be great. Bottom line, if you're wanting to monitor and improve your diet, get it.

title: Absolutely Wonderful!
body: Shop Well has created a great app! I love the ease of being able to pick out the sneaky hidden ingredients just by scanning a product! I can't always read the product lists nor know what some of the ingredients are listed as. This has been a godsend for myself & my family! Even close friends have use this when buying products for me & my children who are very restricted on what they can eat due to allergies. The best part is it keeps getting better as more people submit photos of products....so thankful to just have to snap a photo & submit VS manually put in all the info ourselves......Shop Well, you are wonderful! My daughter loves to use it while we shop as well!

title: I wish...
body: I wish they had a system to let you know when you scan or look at a item on ShopWell that lets you know if you are looking at an item that is either good for what your looking for (example- if you checked that you wanted to be heart healthy, it would let you know that the item is good), has things in it that are things you checked that you do not want much of (such as sugar), or stuff that you checked that you DEFINITELY do not want (like if you are allergic to tree nuts, you don't want that in your food). Other than that the game is great but I wish they would also let you talk to other ShopWell users for tips and so on... It's already a good app but if you make these changes it would be even better!!! üëçüëçüëçüëçüòÑüòÑüòÑüòÑ

title: Heaven for Food Sensitive Shoppers
body: I must rave over this app!  Being gluten sensitive to an extreme, it could take me hours to shop when I needed anything packaged.  Even carefully reading ingredients, sometimes I would miss hidden or less common gluten contamination that could make me acutely sick for days or longer.

title: Great for celiacs!
body: I am newly diagnosed with celiac disease and in learning to navigate my new gluten free world, this app has been a god-send! Those of us who are really sensitive to cross-contamination obviously still need to double check labels, but this makes it so much easier to find the red flags. I have only found one error so far - this app says M&Ms are NOT gluten free (it highlights dextrin as the source of gluten), but according to every Internet forum, plain M&Ms made on a dedicated line are gluten free. Still waiting to hear from the company about the source of their dextrin. Otherwise, ShopWell has been immensely helpful and makes shopping fun! Great way to not only avoid allergens, but also to eat healthily in the process!

title: AWESOME!
body: I've used a ton of health-related apps, and this one will be indispensable among them.  Simply tell the app a bit about yourself and your nutritional preferences, and it'll score foods for you based on how well they meet your needs.  You can browse categories, search, or scan your foods (and see what higher scoring options there are).  You can create shopping lists off of it as well... But this isn't really an all-in-one grocery shopping app, in that it doesn't have prices, stores, etc like you can get in an app like Grocery IQ.  I'll use this app to determine which products I should buy, and use a dif app to create my shopping list of those products.  Very cool and well executed idea.

title: Best download of the year!!!!
body: I have been looking for an app like this for over a year!! I can quickly scan in everything from my pantry, fridge and freezer, create individualized lists & I can select my own personal settings for my healthy lifestyle??? This App is absolutely fantastic! There are a few items from the natural foods store, it would be nice tone able to enter them manually when necessary. Also the ability to transition the lists into actual healthy recipes could take this app to the next level. I have never written a review before, this app deserves the credit!! Great work!

title: Great App!
body: This app cuts your shopping time in half! After you register - you check of your food limitations, scan the products as you shop; and the program determines whether or not you should buy the product. Green light means go ahead and buy it, yellow light means maybe you shouldn't but you can eat it, and finally ready hand means don't buy it!

title: Great app! But I have some requests
body: I love this app. I realized very quickly how poor my diet was and changed my shopping/eating habits instantly! Salads I thought were good are bad, snacks I avoided are in fact fine.

title: Absolute blessing for shopping with new food allergies
body: I was recently diagnosed with Celiacs disease, lactose intolerance, soy intolerance and placed on a low fodmap diet after being extremely sick for years. My doctor recommended this app to help me shop for foods I can eat rather than trying to google 100s of those crazy ingredients and it has been the best experience. This app has most products (even super obscure brands) so it is very easy to use. It even identifies which ingredients are the ones containing my food allergies! It has made recovering so much easier and I will be using this for as long as it's around. Literally the best app ever.

title: good info but app is terrible
body: I have a 6s Plus and I should've known I was in for trouble when I saw it looks horribly stretched out and obviously isn't updated for larger screens - the keyboard is giant and glitchy compared to the normal keyboard actually suited for larger screen sizes

title: Essential to making healthier choices while meal planning!
body: I selected my health goals, food intolerances, and food allergies from the settings menu and not only did this application clearly rate the products I scanned conveniently on my phone from 0-100% aligned with my health goals, it also included easy to see color coding with red being the worst choices for me and green the best.  Obeying the little red stop signal kept inferior foods out of my cart and guided me to select healthier alternatives suggested by the application! I love this application.  It worked well even though my Hy Vee store isn't on their list of stores yet.

title: Great app to find healthy food!!
body: This is an amazing app that will help you find healthy food. The most important benefit I get from Shopwell is the ability to search on virtually any type of food and discover which brands score well for me and which do not. For example - who knew that something like ground meat could score a 92 or a 12 depending on its brand?! (30g of fat in 4oz versus 4.5g from another brand).  WOW!! This app is awesome if you care about what you eat. You can scan items directly in the store, and find out which products are healthy for you.  I love it, thank you shopwell!!!

title: Great app! Needs bigger inventory of foods
body: I love this app. But it needs a bigger inventory of foods. Seems like it only recommends brands that paid to be in the app. Also, should allow you to prioritize the ingredients the are most important and least important in food items. It gave my chobani yogurt a lower score just because it had added sugar but was great on everything other category but scored macaroni and cheese really high. doesn't seem to add up. Also would be great to have an added feature to be able to locate here you can buy some of these recommended items, like if it was tied into grocery stores in the area.

title: Useless!
body: I can read the labels of all the foods I buy at my local grocery store and decide whether I can eat it or not. The problem with this app is that a lot of the items chosen for your specific diet are bought at which local grocery store? It doesn't tell you that! I highly doubt that your grocery list made by this app will be easily found at your favorite grocery store. So are you supposed to run around town to find where each specialty item is located? Not helpful in my eyes.

title: Great App for Gluten Free shopping
body: My fianc√© has Celiac's and shopping Gluten Free has always been difficult. This app makes it very easy to determine if a product has gluten or other allergens without having to spend a lot of time reading labels. There are a few misleading scans (for example, Diet Dr. Pepper comes back as containing gluten, but we know it is Gluten Free), but mostly it does a good job.

title: Almost Perfect
body: This is an essential app for anyone that wants to start shopping smarter for healthier alternatives to the meals you already eat! I use this app every time I shop in the commissary and its helped me learn so much about the nutrition in my diet and how to make it better. My favorite part of this app is that it will give you healthier alternatives to the products you scan. However, it does not tell you where you can find those alternative items. Not sure if this is possible but it's a feature that needs to be added. I mean... What's the point of knowing what to get if you don't know where to get it???

title: Shop well app is bogus
body: This app grades food products, that are full of genetically modified organisms (GMOs), as having high scores and a good choice for you to buy.  BEWARE!  Be informed! Those same companies, that make the products this app grades as great choices, are the ones that support Monsanto and have donated millions to help fight against their products being labeled as containing GMOs.  This app is junk.  Stay away.  Boycott products that have GMOs and the companies that donate money to keep GMO labeling off products.  Download the app Buycott instead to scan which products you should support or avoid.  Its all about money people. Take a stand.  It is cheaper to have GMOs and labeling as having GMOs takes away from their profit margins.  Do your homework.  The offending companies won't do it for you.  Study up on GMOs, Monsanto, prop 37, non-gmo project, etc.

title: Love it
body: I hate going grocery shopping!! After deciding to go wheat free to help with intestinal pain, this app actually prompted me to take a trip to the grocery store! It was so easy to scan items and see if they were wheat free or not. I added animal by-products among ingredients to avoid and was shocked to see how many food items I buy regularly that contain animal by-products. That's just gross.

title: Awesome!
body: My husband and I use this app constantly and it's changing how we shop and eat! It's so easy and fast and helps us make MUCH better choices. He has an intolerance for corn and nuts because of a digestive issue and it's so much faster for him to find products he should avoid AND better choices the app suggests. I try to avoid sugar and I've been amazed at how many foods in the grocery store have added sugar. My favorite part is the better suggestions. It doesn't just tell you to avoid a product; it suggests better, healthier ones. They're usually on the same shelf!

title: Love, but requests
body: Love the app! Some foods I've thought were good for my vegetarian diet have actually turned out to be bad!! One request I have to improve the app, would be to edit your settings so that you can set the grocery stores you shop at. When I scan some things, the app gives me other/healthier recommendations but then says those are only available at Target, Walmart, etc when I only do my grocery shopping at Kroger. Also, maybe give people the option to add foods they scan that the app doesn't recognize, and then we can also put in the nutritional info and ingredients.

title: Wow! It's like having your own personal nutritionist!
body: Just scan the barcode, the App rates the food product based on nutritional value and suggests healthier choices, if there are any.  Also, it explains WHY your choice and the suggested alternatives are healthy or unhealthy.  It even lets you create a shopping list of items for your next trip to the grocery store and which grocery stores nearby have these items!

title: Perfect!
body: I recently had lap band surgery done and am on a low sugar,low fat, high protein diet. Being able to program in my special dietary needs and scan through the rating system is a God send for someone who previously had no clue how to eat healthy. Even when cooking something not so healthy I can still find the most healthiest ingredients to make a meal. The grocery list is a huge help in keeping track of what I need to buy. I have had this app for one week and have already recommended it to several friends who are delighted with it!

title: Awesome oh and read all of it to let you in on. Secret
body: This thing is awesome tells me what has milk in it and helps me from having allergic reaction. And from what I've read people who gave one star don't know what there saying when it's says that it has something like milk or gluten its true some manufactures don't list it or say dairy free but have milk I found a creamer that was dairy free but had dairy and had a allergic reaction. So don't listen to those people who gave it one star. This thing is a life saver. just take your time and learn to use it.

title: Nutrition info at a glance
body: PROs: It seems simple enough to just look at the nutrition facts on labels, but I know I often don't or don't fully consider every detail. It's really great to be able to scan a barcode and have simple color-coded information about how and why something is good for you, or not good for you. I've been surprised multiple times to find things I thought were healthy buys were actually not helping my health goals!

title: Love it
body: I love this app! It's easy to use and has turned me on to so many delicious healthy foods. Plus you will occasionally get an awesome reward for activity.

title: Wow
body: I used this app at the store for the first time today. Sure it's easy to read food labels, but this immediately gives you a rating on the food item depending on what you are trying to watch in you diet. It goes beyond food labels. I had 3 people ask me what app I was using. Our kids even loved using it to scan their food and instantly started making better decisions! We also have a daughter with a food allergy and that was incredible to instantly see things we did not know had some of these allergies in them! Love this app!!!

title: Best App Available!
body: I've never used a more Proficient App! Hopefully lots of people get it a high review...so they are able to obtain more product information! I've spent so much money on apps that don't work...this one is FREE...but worth paying any amount of money to use! Don't have to worry about having my glasses on to read labels then deciding whether item is good for me. Now I scan product & let Shop Well make the decision! Thank you so much for an AMAZING APP! Please help the the other 500,000 other apps out there that don't work! :) Changed my life!

title: Perfect
body: This is the coolest app I have. I am real big in staying healthy and getting the vitamins and foods that are essential to a longer, happier lifestyle. I'm always in the grocery store scanning foods. You would not believe how many foods your eating that claim to be "healthy" that are packed with added sugar, high fructose corn syrup, and preservatives. This really helped me understand a few things about calories, fat, food, and ingredients that I never knew before. There is also "missions" so that you can scan food and get money. At fist I was scanning a bunch of missions but lately there haven't been any new ones?

title: Absolutely amazing
body: I never, and I mean never, rate apps. It's just such a hassle but this app hands down deserves 5 stars. I would even go to the point to rate it 6 stars. It's the ultimate healthy app. You put in what you prefer in your diet & what you want to disclose from it & then helps you with your grocery list. Like I tend to love ice cream and desserts and it'll show me a healthier option that matches my preference but still satisfies my sweet tooth. This is a beautifully designed app and I am truly impressed with it. Great job guys. I'm very pleased.

title: Really Nice!!!
body: Love this app. Especially Great info on alternative selections. Highlighting the bad ingredients is especially helpful when reading the labels. Pop ups are annoying but other than that, great app.   Highly recommended!!!!

title: Too many issues
body: I love this app. It‚Äôs very useful to me...when it works. Half the time I try to use it, it won‚Äôt function. It won‚Äôt load, I can‚Äôt log in, I‚Äôm at the grocery store and it won‚Äôt scan properly...so it kind of defeats the entire purpose of having it. I messaged the app via Facebook today after it once again wouldn‚Äôt allow me to log in, and they said they were having an issue they expected to resolve shortly. That was at 5pm and it‚Äôs  now almost 11pm. I even deleted and reloaded it. It‚Äôs clearly an issue with the app. Kind of disappointing, especially after it was recommended to me by a GI doctor and dietician.

title: Amazing
body: Love this app works wonders on my iPhone 4s I don't usually rate but being able to scan and look up items in my fridge and pantry and being told its good or bad is amazing also the customizable lists that tell you what to get or what to avoid is awesome I find myself scanning most things just wish it had more of a database there are smaller stores that don't sell the brands or the brands they do sell aren't listed I don't normally review apps but this one is amazing the built in shopping list deserves 3 stars by itself

title: Addictive...
body: Very helpful App. Love all the ways you can find ANY item out there. Also like that you can see the nutrition facts and ingredients. This is a good App even just to compare foods when you need to with the healthier option and yet have little time (or patience) in supermarket to stand there and try to read labels, this does it for you in advance, and then you can add the items to a list to know exactly which one you need to just grab off te shelf (with the exception of price comparisons...) I recommens this App.

title: Great healthy eating tool!!
body: Wow! I didn't realize I was making such bad choices. This really simplifies things for you!! Love!

title: My favorite app!   Awesome for Healthy Grocery Shopping! Great Stuff!
body: If you care about your health and eat food, this app is for you.  Love it!

title: Amazing App!
body: This app is one of those apps that had me saying, "Wow! What a smart idea," when I first used it. In practice it's turning out to be very useful and helps me plan my weekly meals according to my weight loss plans and exercise/health goals. My only complaint is that it doesn't recognise the two closest grocery stores - which are chains and not local. This makes for some uncertainty on whether or not the store will have exactly what I've added to my list. Other than that, wonderful.

title: Stunned!
body: Wow. I just have say that I've only had this app for 10 minutes and I'm already blown away to the point of immediately writing a review.

title: Love this app
body: I rarely rate apps because I just don't take the time but I LOVE this app. It has so many great features. I thought I was making pretty healthy choices but thanks to this app I am making even better choices and not spending hours reading food labels. One of my favorite features is "why" the food receives the rating and the listing if the better options for me. I use it daily.

title: Wish I could type in specific ingredients I wanted to avoid
body: This app is helpful and healthful, especially for a vegetarian in a meat eating household. But being that I am a vegetarian working towards veganism, I'd like to be able to type in specific ingredients I'd like to avoid like palm oil.

title: Definitely recommend!
body: I have celiac disease and am very sensitive to any amount of gluten. Shop well has made it so that if there is a product which I am not sure is gluten free, I can scan it and it will tell me. Also, for awhile I was on a low FODMAP diet and Shopwell gives you the option to select that so it will avoid certain foods. If you have any allergy, are on any type of diet, or want to manage special types of vitamins that you are in taking, I definitely recommend this app!

title: WHY DID YOU CHANGE IT!!
body: Almost every week I would make a list on shopwell (not the app, the website) but now they completely got rid of the website and I was forced to get the app! But that's not all, you USED to be able to browse food that would fit your diet and trade one thing for another, BUT BOW YOU CANT!!

title: Shop Well
body: I'm really new to this app so I recognize that there's still a lot I hv not learned yet, but my suggestion is that once you customize it, those food options should no longer show up. So, for example, if I can't hv grains, don't show me the big AVOID sign, show me my options & if I hv none, show the AVOID sign when I go to that category (& since programmers can do just about anything, hv the category go away if there are no options & possibly encourage users to offer alternatives if the app doesn't hv any.) Otherwise it's an awesome tool!!

title: The Best ever grocery app
body: I totally love, love ShopWell! It is now my go-to app when figuring out what foods to put in my shopping cart üçéüçäüçßüçâüçìüçÜ and for building my shopping list.  All you need  to do is scan the barcode on a food and it tells you how well it scores for you.  Thumbs up and amazing!  It is üëçüòÑ for allergies or just eating healthy.  Yup, the personal choices actually account for my food goals unlike every other app I have tried.  This should be a paid app!   Download!  You won't regret.

title: Has value but not meeting all my needs
body: This app is absolutely fantastic for the health factor! For me personally, in order to stay efficient with the little free time I have, I need one quick list for all items I'll be getting at the grocery store. Unfortunately, this app only allows one to track actual groceries, necessitating a second list for cleaning products, paper products, etc. May not be a problem for some, however, it is for me. Otherwise, this is a fabulous app!!!

title: CEO of One
body: Love love love this app. I found myself scanning the entire pantry, and WOW was I ever surprised, it's full of all the wrong stuff!!! In keeping with my personal goals I found the shopping list and where I can find items that are truly better for me super handy.  I highly  recommend.... just wish I could add additional food allergies above and beyond the standardized list. In addition, it would be awesome to have the capabilities to add additional household members who have different  dietary needs.

title: Really easy and useful
body: There are a ton of foods out there, and many of them have a ton of ingredients and nutrient info.  What does it all mean, and what does it mean to me?  This app does a good job helping me sort through the clutter and find more foods that are a good fit for my needs.  I've used it before, and now i'll use it more often since they started offering rewards that show up every so often when I use it to find out about the food I'm thinking of buying.

title: Just a suggestion
body: I just got this app, I have only scanned two items, one I knew was going to be good for me, here is what I didn't like. If I scan a cereal that isn't good for my diet, why would it suggest a whole grain pizza and not another cereal that would be good? Would make sense to suggest something in the same category that you are scanning. I like it otherwise and believe that it will be helpful in losing weight and staying away from lactose.

title: Almost awesome
body: I love this app. It is highly helpful and provides immediate feedback that is much faster than googling individual products. This app would get 5 stars except for a few things. Although dietary preferences can be selected the feedback is still bias towards traditional diets that I do not follow. For example, on my list of red "avoids" saturated fat is not checked. However it still appears in the feedback as a red frown face and is factored into the match. Also I would like there to be a "carbohydrate" or "high sugar" Avoid option, or a "low carb" option under the Wants tab.

title: Download this apppppp!!!!!!!
body: I have used this app for a month now and it is SOOO helpful!! I have celiac disease, a gluten intolerance, and I am into cross contamination and all of that. I can always count in this app, it has every little detail of gluten listed and it is amazing! It even lists cross contamination which is great for people with celiac. There are a lot of other allergens as well that you can add to your profile so you can have it check for those things in your food. DOWNLOAD THIS APPPPP!!!!

title: Timesaver, Lifehack at its best
body: The app seems like it is still a work in progress. But it is a great tool for checking what ingredients are in line with your health needs, as you dictate in setting your profile. The categories of menu items to avoid or items you want to include in your diet are a bit too broad for me. With some tweaking, this app will help to eliminate  anymore wasted time on fact-searching for products at grocery stores!!!!

title: Great Service!
body: I was immensely pleased with the overall service. The app allows you to filter out foods based in dietary preferences, restrictions, or needs. They offer health tips as well. When I chose to delete my account, the response was very friendly (and sent after less than 24 hours, which is pretty quick to me). If you need information on what to shop for as you're shopping, this app is definitely helpful.

title: Great Tool ‚Ä¢ One Suggestion
body: This is great app. My gf and I have created a system using Shopwell every time we go grocery shopping.

title: BEST APP EVER Invented!!!!!! Would recommend to anyone and everyone.
body: I just got this app and I am addicted to it! Lately, I have been reading up on nutrition and was curious to see what kind of apps were available. I found this one and it is incredible!!!!!! And FREE!! I love it because I can set my preferences and allergies. I am allergic to soy and with the barcode scanner I find that most of my foods have soy. I'd recommend this app to anyone including the healthiest person on earth!!!!!! <3 <3 <3

title: Love this app a lot!
body: I love this ShopWell app! I recommend taking the time to make your food list by category (dairy, breads, etc), which makes shopping easier.  There are name brands I am not familiar with, but I add them to the list because they are 100% in meeting my goals, then I add ones I am familiar with that my store carries that may be at 86%, just in case I can't find the 100% name brands.  I am beginning to care for myself being health conscience & this app is helping simplified my shopping needs without reading labels.

title: In Love!
body: This app has made shopping healthy SO MUCH easier!!! I can make a list according to my scores (based on my age, gender, health preferences, food allergies) and have everything right there. No more reading label after label in the grocery store searching for some product that meets my strict guidelines. I even realized some foods I was buying weren't the best for me. I didn't have a clue until Shopwell informed me. Wow! This is now my favorite app. I'm so glad I downloaded it!

title: Great App, 1 Suggestion
body: I love this app! I downloaded it a few hours ago and have been scanning everything in my kitchen to make sure I was eating as well as thought!

title: Great app but a few bugs to work out
body: I love that I can look up the nutrition of foods I buy and see how the ingredient list. I love that there is a score on how healthy the food is. I love that the app highlights the preservatives and other ingredients that are not so good. However, there are redundant food items, which often times has different scores even though its the same item. Cheerios is an example. Also, there are some items that I could not find, such as Smart Chicken or Delish rising crust pizza.

title: Best inspirational app for those who look for clean eating!
body: This app works amazing! If you're looking to eat healthy but don't know too much about what you want, this is the app for you. It asks you what you're trying to watch, what you're looking for, basically sets it's health rating on YOU and even gives you recommendations! I am in love with this app, it's very helpful while dieting to just simply trying to improve your eating habits!

title: Read this!
body: This app is a good idea but they need to re-do it. There are many things terribly wrong. For example, if an item has added sugar it is docked points. This is good but they dock it the same amount if it has 20 g added sugar or if it has 1 g added sugar. There are cereals with 15 g sugar that are rated better than similar cereals with 5 g sugar because they have a little more iron. This app also does not take into account calories or portion size. There are veggie burgers with 300 calories and 15 g protein rated higher than veggie burgers with 100 calories and 10 g protein. This doesn't make sense. I have found numerous examples like this. I hope no one is basing what they eat on this app!

title: What a Help!
body: This is such a terrific app! Put in your own personal goals to customize and I have been constantly surprised by the results of things I've been buying - sometimes items are better than I thought. The scan piece is wicked fast too so you can balance item and scan in a millisecond instead of laying it perfectly flat and looking like a tool at the grocery store

title: Love it so far!
body: Having so many food allergies, this is extremely helpful when avoid the top 8 food allergens and more. Even when you are use to reading nutrition labels, this app makes that even easier, saving time and making quick decisions while out grocery shopping. I've noticed that some odd brands aren't listed but that's expected since they can't do EVERYTHING!

title: Just installed
body: And so surprised how helpful it will be for me!! I usually read the nutrition info on each new product figuring out how healthy it is for my all-the-time-weight-watching )))) Now I can learn everything when I have time, saving huge time at supermarkets !!! Thank you for the app! When I start using it more actively I might have something else to write here. For now I love the idea after quick acquaintance with the app.

title: Room to Grow
body: This app is on its way to being good. As more people use it, I expect the choices, menu options and demographic features offered will expand. The scanner has trouble recognizing some barcodes (but searching for the product turns up the desired result usually) and, sadly, I sometimes cannot find the suggested alternatives in my area. Overall, it's another great tool that helps rank foods based on personalized preferences. An app will never replace common sense and general nutrition knowledge.

title: Wow
body: I like the feature that has this app providing suggestions of better options. I am a label-reader when I shop, but it's time consuming to read every single label. With this app, I can scan one product then get information about OTHER similar products which may be a better choice for me without having to read more labels or take time searching. Wonderful!

title: Looooovvvve this app!!!
body: This app is so wonderful! Im trying really hard to eat healthier and this app can help me do just that. I love the scan feature and i love that it tells me why something isnt a good match for you based on my preferences. Im going to use this everytime i shop now. The one thing i wish it had was a feature that shows me where to buy products in my area. That would be a great feature to add.

title: Transforms Grocery Shopping
body: I wish I had this when I first started my healthy eating journey!! I am pretty good at eyeballing healthy choices, but this takes it to another level. Every where you look, there is another useful button to make the annoying chore of grocery shopping that much easier. As a personal trainer, it will help my clients make better choices & not feel as overwhelmed.

title: FANTASTIC
body: I'm so happy I came across this app! Being that its a New Year and one of my goals is to eat healthier, this app has made it so much easier! So easy to use and keeps your list of foods that are good for you, so the next the next time you go to a store, all you need to do is take a look at that list!!! Everyone should def have this app on their phone if they are looking to get healthy and feel better!

title: Not very personalized at all
body: It's pretty and easy to use. Even though I didn't check the "avoid high fat" it gives low scores to high fat foods. Don't assume everyone has the same goals. If I want to personalize it to my high fat diet, let me do so, or don't tell me it's customizable. It also needs a bigger data base. Or let people enter their own foods and add to the database. I scanned two snack bars, one by larabar and one by Rise and it didn't recognize either. Great idea. Poor implementation. Hopefully it'll improve and I can use this in the future. For now it won't waste space on my device.

title: Nutrition made easy
body: A wonderful app, I scan most things to look for gluten and healthier options at the supermarket. this app also covers several different stores so you can see different products other stores may carry. It really helps me out when I am questionable as if something has gluten in it at all... Soy sauce... Who knew?! There are several products in the system, I'd say for every ten items I scan two to three do not go through. 4/5

title: This app should cost $100+
body: We have an 11 year old with EOE.  He started to vomit after every meal. We took him to a specialist, put him on multiple drug strategies.  None of them worked. Worked with his nutritionist, got the Elimination-Diet no(dairy, soy, eggs, wheat, nuts, tree nuts, fish, shellfish). We were lost until our nutritionist told us about the app. It gives us so many options including less expensive stores.

title: Amazing
body: This app is fantastic. I have recently been out on an anti inflammatory diet with zero gluten. I wanted to cry walking around the grocery store. I'm not supposed to have corn, soy, dairy, eggs, or Guten grains. This has made shopping so much easier! And I love that it gives me ideas of things I can have. I think everyone with an allergy or sensitively would benefit greatly from this app. I honestly can't believe it's free. Thank you so much!

title: Absolutely love this app!!
body: Sooo helpful! Just have a couple complaints. One is that they need to add foods from fresh and easy. I do a lot of my shopping there and they do not have the store brand in the system. I'd love to be able to select to avoid meat products. I'm a vegetarian and a lot of products sneak meat in them and it would be nice to be able to not have to worry about reading all labels! Please add :) either way the app is still awesome and one of a kind!

title: Very helpful
body: You always think you know what you are buying at the store...to do it correctly you could be there for hours reading every label...exhausting. Shopping the perimeter of the market is easy...fruit/vegetables-good, meat-keep it lean, bakery-whole grain or keep on walking, dairy-low fat & watch the sugar...This makes healthy food shopping easy especially when purchasing packaged foods. Try it!

title: Love the app
body: Takes the guess work out of trying to pick the better choice!  I am trying to lose weight and am slowly going off gluten.  I have other health issues that make it necessary to wean myself off the gluten instead of just cutting it out completely. Not everything I have scanned is in there but enough that I am able to make good choices.

title: Great for everyone!
body: This app lets you pick different goals. It works for both me and my husband while shopping. Used it today for my grocery order. Took a little longer in the store...but what I would normally buy ended up being a weak match, and it showed me stronger/better matches. Same price, same kind of product, different ingredients. Better healthy life. Love!

title: Doesn't open all the time
body: Why does this app take forever to open, it just keeps saying "signing in"!! This is very frustrating when you're doing your grocery shopping and am trying to find Gluten Free items because a family member has Celiac Disease. Please fix this asap I have been using this app for a few years now, I use it all the time, and when it works it's a wonderful tool, but when I can't use it to check foods it's extremely frustrating.

title: Life-saver
body: Thank you! Thank you! Thank you! This ap is a life-saver for me and my family, trying to manage feeding a toddler with multiple food allergies! Especially love that you can scan products, search for them, and even find alternatives. It even scores them nutritionally AND tells you where you can find items nearby. Makes "reading" labels so much easier!!

title: Using the App
body: A friend recommended the app and at first I couldn't figure out how to use it but now I take it shopping with me. It's still building its database and if you'll add products, it will help all of us. The ones it's listed have been great, especially on those words that you aren't sure of, a quick scan tells you what they are and after completing your profile to avoid allergens (I have many) it works well.

title: Nice app, but......
body: I would have gave this app 5 stars-it's easy to scan items,  provides great information on what's makes an item healthy vs unhealthy and has great recommendation for healthy items. The one down side is that it makes you sign in every time you open the app. Why can't it leave you signed in? I'm  usually in a rush at the grocery store and I just want to scan an item and go!! Please fix this, then your app is perfect!!

title: Life saver!
body: This app has literally saved my life! I have a number of food allergies, making it very difficult to walk into a grocery store and shop with ease. Shop well allows you to scan the item and search for the product to see if it fits your dietary needs. The app is easy to use and finds the hidden ingredients in all food. It also rates how healthy it is for you!! Love. Love. Love!!

title: A lifesaver
body: This app is wonderful. After a life threatening illness that baffled the docs, I found an integrative physician that suspected food. I ditched the scripts and started a clean diet. Who knew soy was hidden in so many common foods?

title: What a revelation!!!
body: Amazing!!! I scan any food at the grocery store and instantly see if it has what I want, or the things I am trying to avoid! I found out the frozen waffles I'd been buying had nasty trans fats and high fructose corn syrup, but the other brand was totally healthy (and tastes better!) I am gonna recommend this app to all my friends who are trying to eat better :D This makes it easy!

title: Needs something else but very good app
body: I love the app!! But I think it needs more profiles like for example I have 2 kids ages 1 and 3 have a husband who is type 1 diabetic think it would b nice to have more then one profile or make it to where u can combine the profiles or something to see which is good for everyone instead of just one person. Other then that I love this app!

title: This app is great!
body: This app helps my mom and I pick out the right foods at the grocery store. I noticed lots of false advertising and being only 10 years old I find this app very impressive. I noticed lots of foods our family usually eats has HIGH SODIUM and TRANS FATS. I recommend this app to anyone who is trying to eat healthier, controlling weight management or just looking for the right foods. Thank you. üòä

title: Great
body: Love it!Cant afford certain programs so this app is a great help. Im able to go through my pantry and see what i should or should not continue to buy with the scan feature, i can creat my grocery list, and it provides better options for the things i shouldn't buy. This is so wonderful for a beginner like me. If you're ready to start this healthy journey please download!

title: Amazing that it is free!
body: Gets 5 star because it is free. I always wanted an app like this but many you have to pay for or join some program. My only complaint is that items with scores between 70, they don't explain why it doesn't get an 100. Would love to know that. Other than that thank you. Boxes lie about being healthy and low calorie and you guys tell the truth!

title: Great app!
body: Well this solved my mystery of why I was getting so many headaches. My diet this week was packed with soy, and I am allergic but wasn't checking my products closely as I should. I know you can just read it yourself. But this is easy, takes some of the guesswork out for you, and it gives you some alternatives.

title: I used to love the app
body: I'm quite disappointed in the new update. When I scanned things today it kept popping up as having dairy, gluten and wheat! So I hit the ingredients button and it's reading "sunflower butter" and classifying it as dairy because it says "butter". To me, they're tried to make a shortcut, thus, providing inaccurate information and ultimately very poor customer service. The missions are gone, as well. I enjoyed doing them. Please correct the ingredient "sensitivity" and bring back the more accurate scanning process. Thank you.

title: Just what I was looking for
body: Awesome app! Let's you select your food allergies, intolerance or goals and then gives you detailed information about specific products you scan or browse based on your settings. The best part is, it highlights all the "bad stuff" out of the ingredient's list, contains full nutritional information and gives you healthier alternatives!

title: Fantastic app (few suggestions)
body: First discovered this app from a parent as a way to assist their child identify foods that could be potentially harmful while at school. I now use it for myself as well and it saves me from a lot of researching and planning before and while shopping. My only Suggestion would be to be able to save multiple profiles on the same acct.

title: Very helpful
body: This app has safe my life for I have terrible food allergies and even more terrible eye site!! And at the store it's hard enough to see all the ingredients because it's sometimes a lot to read or hidden words that companies use to refer to certain things I can't consume.  It's very helpful and I appreciate it very much.  To the creators of this app hats off!!!

title: Great free app
body: Is a great app that helps you sort through most products.

title: AmaZing must-have App! Very helpful. Only wish database included Wal-Mart & Target brand food.
body: I couldn't believe how helpful this app is when it comes to making better food choices. Our country NEEDS more tools like this to help fight heart disease and other illnesses caused by making poor choices in food. HIGHLY recommend!!! Thanks for helping us move towards the right direction in our overall health and well-being = )

title: Amazing!
body: I have several allergies including dairy, gluten, and peanuts.  This app lets you select your allergies and find food thAt you can eat, but not only that, it can help you eat healthy by helping you select that you want to avoid several foods such as sugar and trans fat.  I would highly recommend this app for those with allergies or those who just want to eat healthy.

title: Healthy Eating Tool!
body: Shopwell is a wonderful app to have of you eat healthy or want to start eating healthy. It gives you rewards for finding or scanning healthy foods and gives you great rewards.

title: AMAZING APP
body: This is a great app!!! It tells you everything! It is perfect for me because I am an athlete and this app helps me pick out the things I should and should not eat. The only thing I wish this app showed me was where to get the food because I am allergic to soy and tree nuts and a lot of the items that come up I have never heard of them in my life, so it's hard to find the product by myself but besides that this is an amazing app!

title: One suggestion
body: It would be very nice if you could filter products by what has the most/least for an item. For example, carbohydrates are an issue for my family. If I were able to search for bread and filter it by which had the least amount of carbs I would be more than willing to give this app 5 stars. It's a really good app and I'm excited to see it continue to improve.

title: Better Choices
body: This is what Apple apps are supposed to be!  This makes shopping so much easier especially for those in training who need healthy options. I need 200g daily of protein and this helps me find better options as well as unknown sources. Love that foods are scored. I wish there are even more foods listed or perhaps a fast food version.

title: Great app.
body: I use it every time I go grocery shopping. They don't have have very many generic brands (Kirkland, market pantry) but they have a good amount of information on the more popular brands. You can customize the types of foods that fit into your diet and it will give you a score of a product, once scanned, based of the information you provide.

title: üí¢EXCELLENTüí¢
body: Totally new to eating GF & this app is a MUST HAVE. Love how you just scan any food & it tells you if GF. Plus it has ratings so you can pick & choose your foods. The shopping list being linked to the foods is WONDERFUL. If you've scanned a food & want to add it to your grocery list...it's just a finger tap away. Thank you for making a major health issue & diet change easy to do!!

title: Exactly what I was looking for
body: Trying to eat healthier and understanding the nutrition label can be tough. This app takes the guess work out!

title: Simply amazing!
body: This app is by far one of the most useful one's I've got!  Due to my inability eat or drink anything containing lactose and a new found inability to ingest gluten I've struggled figuring out what I can and cannot have anymore.  Now I'm not worried if I can have this or have that!  It has an abundance of items and suggestions on foods I can eat!  Made my life just a tad easier :)

title: Can I trust it?
body: It is a stellar concept but less than satisfactory execution. It seems that if it is not a major brand it‚Äôs not listed and if it is listed the major brand gets a better rating. I scanned some juice that had no additives it was rated very much lower than a major brand with more additives than you can shack a stick at. Than sativa is an artificial sweetener. Really! That brings the whole app into question. What else do they have wrong. In my opinion I can‚Äôt trust the app to give me good information, therefor it is of limited use. Hopefully I will be able to trust it sometime in the future.

title: One improvement
body: I was just diagnosed with high blood pressure and cholesterol.  This app is really helpful to make better choices. I would suggest an area where you can search for a specific item rather than having to sort by product name. It takes way too long to scroll through all that is listed. Otherwise seems to be very helpful

title: Not Gluten-accurate
body: I cant have gluten, so I was SO excited about this app... until I tried it. Like a kid with a new toy, I started scanning everything in my pantry. Items were coming up as "containing gluten" when the item package was CLEARLY labeled "gluten free". Last night I scanned some ice cream (just for fun), your app said it contained wheat & gluten.. NOT ONE ingredient listed would've contained wheat or gluten. PLEASE fix this! Or at least have a way for users to leave a comment on specific items. I will be deleting the app til bugs are fixed. Such a shame.

title: Love most aspects but needs some updates!
body: I love the capabilities of the app for me to parameter off the food options & %s of acceptability, however it would be far superior to scan the product, select the product for your list, & the current price displayed. I haven't found this function & if I missed it, I'll take helpful guidance to find it. If it isn't there it would be a great "add".

title: Great but needs an update
body: I've used this app for awhile now (a year?). I have celiac disease and can't have gluten. The ease is scanning a barcode makes my grocery trips and meals at friends houses SO much easier.

title: Love this app
body: I have used this app several times and I'm so glad I did. There have been so many foods that it had gluten in it, and decided to check. Sure enough they had gluten. It has been a God send. I just scan the label (takes a little practice to learn how to get the label where you need it) and right away it will tell me if there's gluten in it.

title: ShopWell  - Healthy diet & Grocery Food
body: Tomas Enrique Sanchez Sanchez is glad to use this application to use appropriately the list of my food while , I go shopping with my favorite Food list. There are excellent calcium food to use appropriately on each Food. I'll give 5 stars for this application . I'll recommend my friends to add this application on their iPhones, computer and tablets.

title: Healthy choices
body: I am very impressed by this app. While at the grocery store all I have to do is scan a product and it tells me if it is a good choice based on the dietary profile I created. what I also love is the healthier alternatives it gives me. I know I will be making healthier food purchases at the grocery store!!! Here's to looking and feeling Great!!!

title: Love it so far !
body: Just got it today. No glitches yet. It's got so many cool features including the ability to build a customized nutrition profile and scan barcodes of items to see how well it may match with your individual needs ‚ò∫Ô∏è‚ò∫Ô∏è this is what I've been looking for ! Also love the tips page

title: Awesome App
body: This app is exactly what I have been looking for! The gluten feature makes it a great tool for Celiacs or those with gluten intolerance, makes determining if a food is safe a breeze! The rating system is great if your interested in how healthy the foods you are consuming are, all based on your dietary needs/wants. Download it, you won't be disappointed!!

title: Love it for the most part
body: I live the app for myself... I have scanned a few items for my son (10 months) like these yogurt melts and teethers. I realize the app isn't meant for baby type food but would be nice of there was some option for those. We homemake mostly everything so the snack type stuff we could use a little guidance on. One item I have removed from my diet after using this- fig nutons!

title: Wonderful.
body: This app is amazing. I only wish you could have multiple user accounts to click between so that I could find foods applicable to all individuals in my family instead of just for myself. Also maybe an element that shows what fruits and veggies are in season.  Though, I am quite amazed with the app simply as it is.

title: I would give it a 5 but a few things...
body: It doesn't have p/l brands like Publix and we eat a lot of those.  Also when I do a search I want more comprehensive info to compare things with for instance I searched Halls Drops but it only came up sugar free. I didn't want sugar free and Shopwell didn't recognize my 2 brands. I need to check my current house items for gluten to know to stay away from it later. Thx!

title: Incredibly Helpful!
body: This app is fantastic! As someone who was recently put on a gluten free diet in an area which doesn't really support gluten free living I've been struggling. I spend triple the amount if time in grocery stores reading labels! But now I can quickly scan using this app and find out what items risk my health! Worth your time, support, and free download!

title: Awesome and useful!
body: Using the app now to lose the weight gained during pregnancy. Also continuing to manage carb intake due to high numbers during post-pregnancy glucose challenge. Really important to manage now to avoid getting type 2 diabetes making this app a lifesaver. Really loving the fact that I can now see what stores have he products I want.

title: Great app, BUT...
body: This app is excellent in how it caters to specific dietary needs, but it definitely needs to improve in accuracy. For example, I have an allergy to soy, so I use almond milk instead. When I scan the barcode for the almond milk, it lists it as containing soy, even though the ingredients say otherwise. I would recommend this app to anyone who doesn't have specific food allergies until they get more precise.

title: BEST APP EVER!
body: This app completely rocks! I am already skinny so I don't need it for that, but I need to stay fit, because I do cross-country and health is just overall important to me! So if you feel like health is a big part, or even a medium part of your life, download this amazing app! It finds the perfect products for you and you specifically! This is awesomest app ever! Definetly reccomend!

title: FANTASTIC!
body: It's wonderful to be in the grocery store, pick up an item you think would be good for, scan it, & know, not only whether that item fits in your goals & how well, but also be able to see the best item you could purchase instead.  I don't have waste a bunch of wasted time reading all the labels.

title: Misleading product reviews
body: I think you should revise the way you word the product summaries - they are misleading. For instance, a product containing a lot of protein but also a ton of preservatives and GMO additives is not an "excellent source of protein", it's a product with a very high amount of protein; there are certainly other healthy products that are truly 'excellent sources' of protein and are overall more nutritious. Please consider this change; the philosophy behind this app is otherwise great.

title: This is the app I have been looking for
body: I have several food sensitivities. The only one missing from the list is MSG. Hoping this is added on the next upgrade. This stuff is in every thing and has so many names now do to sneaky food makers. I can not have it it gives me bad head aches and makes my skin feel like it is crawling. Looking forward to shopping faster with this app. Thanks.

title: Love it!
body: I have just been put on a gluten free diet and this app is MORE THAN helpful! I can go to the grocery store and just scan something i don't know if gluten free and it will pop up and say "avoid" you just put in what your allergic to,  for example : nuts or dairy (etc) and it will tell you avoid the product. It is amazing and so wonderful. A lifesaver! HIGHLY RECOMMEND THIS APP!!!!!

title: Great incredibly helpful ap!
body: I use this app because I have to eat gluten-free.  it's so incredibly helpful when I'm at the store to scan a barcode and it (the app) immediately tell me whether or not the product has gluten in it as opposed to be reading through all the ingredients I highly recommend this if you were on a restricted diet

title: AMAZING!
body: I absolutely LOOOVE this app! I can't eat gluten and reason very single label is exhausting so this app is awesome. You just scan look at the ingredient list and it tells you if it does or does not have gluten in it. Since it works for other allergies and has a variety of settings it is useful for just about anyone! Did I mention its FREE?! Can't get better

title: One of my favorite apps!
body: I absolutely love this app- I rely on it while grocery shopping now because of the barcode scanner. I have a lactose intolerance and I find this app incredibly helpful in alerting me to finding hidden milk and dairy. If you have a food allergy or always try to find the healthiest item out there in a sea of choices, you NEED this app.

title: Consider adding mPoints?
body: Awesome app! Just wondering, since you have an achievements system already in place, will you be adding "mPoints" in the future? I'm not affiliated with them, and heard about this through the "Nexercise" app. I think it might be a great way to encourage people to use this app and for users to gain real rewards from their achievements.

title: Great App
body: Fantastic app.  Does everything it is supposed to do and then some.  Only a few barcodes didn‚Äôt scan and that was because that was the store brand.  I was amazed to see all the ‚Äúextra‚Äù things are added to products that I thought were ‚Äúpure‚Äù.

title: Latest update
body: I love love love this app! I have celiac disease and frequently used this app to help guide my choices.  It has a ton of info on gluten free products and, while I still check product boxes for changes in ingredients, I definitely use it every time I buy groceries!

title: Helps me avoid alergies
body: This app is great... It helps me find foods that have hidden allergens in them and make it much easier than reading through the entire label

title: So far so good
body: I've only used this for a couple shopping outings. I tested it around my house scanning products I knew were and were not part of the diet plan. It has passed the test so far. I am also a dietitian. I have recommended this app to families with allergies and Celiac, and they've had great success. This is the first time I've used it for FODMAP. Bravo!

title: Informational & incredibly useful nutrition app.
body: Love this app. Virtually eliminates the need to read the back if every product you question if it may or may not be good to put into your body. Even has a setting to add products onto a shopping list and text or email it to yourself. Great job whoever created this one!

title: Great for gluten free beginners!
body: There is so much to learn when you must be gluten free and this app is making it very easy to get started.  It would be nice if I could go straight to the bottom of a list when I do a search. For example when I did a search for yogurt I got about a million results and it took forever to get to the bottom of the list where the yoplait products were.

title: Suggestion
body: Can you make it possible to look for specific ingredients. I am trying to avoid xanthum gum which seems to be almost everything processed.  Or someone might have to avoid a specific dye in food. I know that gets more complicated. Thanks. For a great app. You also have a listing for gluten free but not vegetarian or vegan. Can u add these ?

title: Excatly what I want
body: I cook for my parents and my mum has high blood pressure. This app is perfect because it shows what has added sugar and too high of sodium. I've always shopped healthy but now its ten times easier becaue I know the app gives me the next option up for a healthier product. And I love the point system, it helps me visualize and compair.

title: Wonderful App!
body: This app is super easy to use, even for beginners!  You can look specific things up or just browse categories. Biggest downfall is that the vast majority of products don't have stores indicated where they can be found. Add that and the average price of items and this app would be absolutely perfect!  Maybe in the next update these will be included.

title: Beware BEWARE
body: If you have celiac or gluten issues.  Beware. They have an issues with the ingredient showing things that are and sometimes are not in the product you are scanning. I was just trusting this scanner and have payed the price. Please read the labels when it comes to allergies because no product like this one is fail proof. I was NOT eating things  when in fact I could have been and then eating things that said they had NO WHEAT in them when in fact THEY DID.

title: Gluten checking
body: I have been reading labels for years and still have problems! With hope this app will help me stop being sick even a little bit! It is nice to be able to watch my health while I am watching for that rascals who hide gluten on us. Thank you very much for making this available to me!

title: Great App
body: I'm living on my own and doing my food  own shopping for the first time. I was overwhelmed at first with all of the options and never knew the right thing to get to fit my healthy lifestyle. This app has helped a lot with showing me all the best options and making a grocery list to take with me!

title: A great app to help new Celiac diagnosis parents
body: Our daughters and maybe the wife have slight to major wheat sensitivities.  I need an app to warn me about poor food choices and offer suggestions.  This does that and more.  The bar scanning, profile setup and health advise is so helpful.

title: Like it a lot.
body: I have been using ShopWell since January and I really like it. I have found a lot of new foods to try that have less sodium (hubby has high blood pressure). and had no idea how much hidden sugar was in regular food. Now I'm obsessed to get my sugar stats down each week. Definitely a good app for grocery shopping.

title: Excellent for celiacs!
body: I use this as my safety net when I'm shopping or as a double check when someone else has done the shopping for me. It has saved me from being exposed to gluten numerous times and helped me find gluten free jellybeans at Easter! Love this application!! I'd pay for it if it wasn't free. I appreciate the updates as well. Thank you!!!

title: Helpful app
body: This has been a helpful app for me in a couple of ways. One, my diet is based on a lot of fruit in the morning and evening, and the app has helped steer me away from higher calorie fruits like grapes. Two, I've got a perpetual problem remembering whether it's saturated or unsaturated fat that's a problem, and the grades sort it out quickly.

title: Helpful but needs some adjustments
body: This app is great but it would be nice to see how much food costs at different stores.  It would also be beneficial to have a more extensive list of health problems and things that people need to limit, but not completely eliminate.  I am hypothyroid and I should limit gluten, almonds and soy so it would be nice if I could monitor that through this app.

title: Ok
body: This app is ok.  It needs way more in its database.  Things I know for sure/ have the words written on it that the product is Gluten Free... Does not come up.  Tried scanning most things in my kitchen as for we just switched over to Gluten Free food because of my sons recent diagnosis for Celiac and nothing is came up.  I don't know if because the products are off brands and not popular General Mills or pillsbury products.  But I would hope that they would have all the off brands Gluten free products (ex Cup4cup flour... carried at William Sonoma) listed. Good thing this app is free!

title: Great.
body: I love this app. I'm a big health person and work out all the time, so this app. Really helped me to learn about what was in everything I'm buying. You can type or scan something you want and it'll score it according to your wants. It's also a good app. for people who have diabetes.

title: Love this app
body: This makes it easy to educate yourself to the foods you need for your diet or whatever your specific needs are:) if you have a smart phone just download the app and you can check on some of foods you are eating and bring it shopping to find the best match. This is just sooo cool you havta try it;)

title: Very good app!
body: Here's what I think: great app, however it would be wonderful that once products are added to my shopping cart, they could be categorized into food types. They seem to be added in the order they are placed in the cart and it makes it difficult to later find particular items I added. Thanks for a good health food app!

title: Keeping me on track!
body: Loving how the app now links with my Instacart and Safeway card -- all of my purchases are there for me to see with healthier choices recommended -- talk about keeping me honest! :)

title: Love it!
body: I've only had it for a few days and it's already making me make healthy choices. Not only can you use it in the grocery store but you can use it at your house if your trying to find something to eat and you want it to be healthy.

title: Great!
body: It's actually free its not those stupid apps that are free todownload then u have 2 pay to use . You type in what ingredients u want to avoid then scan products and it'll say if it is good if not gives u better options I was shocked that some foods I thought were healthy weren't , good to know ,great app!

title: Easily make customized, educated food choices
body: When grocery shopping, I often wonder how specific foods and brands truly compare to each other and Shopwell takes the guesswork out of it. My cart is filled with better choices for my whole family.

title: Game changing App
body: Wow! Can't thank you guys enough I've been using shopwell for a while now. First just to help me pick out foods for my children (single dad) but since I've been using it I've been making smarter decisions for myself. I've now lost 42 pounds and counting. Consider it my favorite app for anything food!

title: Has potential
body: Allow users to put in their actual ages and not just ranges.  There's a huge gap between 18 and 49.  Consider race and ethnicity since some factors run through those lines specifically.  Add more categories.  I didn't see fruits right away if it is a choice.  Add more food choices.  Every city doesn't sell the same products.  Allow users to put in more personal information, like weight.

title: Useful but needs to be for whole family
body: Seems to be a very useful app that helps me stay more on track with groceries.  However, I'd really really love it if the app designers would make it where I could add other members of my family onto my profile to make sure I'm shopping for them as well!  If that option was added if definitely give it a 5 star...please consider this!

title: Ok
body: The only thing that would make this app better would be the ability to add your own list of allergic foods. I recently found out I'm allergic to 24 different foods, including pork, beef, yeast, sugar cane and iceberg lettuce, to name a few.  I'm allergic to so much I have to carry an epipen. Sometimes I can't remember all of the things I'm allergic to, and certainly not when I'm shopping.  I'll try this out for a while to see how it works.

title: Reason for a 4 star and not 5
body: I would have given this app a five star since I have used it before on my husbands iPod and i loved it but when I got an iPad it was difficult to use because the screen is small and when you enlarge it everything is pixelated. If this app was for the iPad as well i would have given it a five star.

title: AMAZING, just what I need
body: This app is amazing and proven to be a potential life saver literally. Haven't gotten an official diagnosis yet but I'm pretty sure Im showing signs of Celiac Disease and this breaks down all the foods I can eat without gluten , PLUS give me healthy foods to change my overall diet!! Applause to the makers of this. Itd be nice to see prices but Keep it up!!

title: So so app
body: I used to love this app and would have given it more stars, but it seems almost impossible to use. It constantly freezes up when I scan an item, and half the things I scan have no rating. It worked better before all the updates, now it's a huge waste of time and the constant pop up rewards are annoying! I think it's time to look for something that actually saves shopping time.

title: Fantastic app for those with an allergy!!
body: This is a great app if you have an allergy!  I have a gluten allergy and this app is quick and totally reliable.  Set your profile, what you want to avoid and scan away!!   It's quick, easy and very convenient.   I've recommended this to all of my friends.

title: Great App
body: This is a wonderful and very informative app. I use it all the time now. My daughter was just diagnosed with Celiacs so this is very helpful. The only thing I would like to see added would be personal hygiene products. Shampoo and lotions and such also have gluten. Would love to see a category for this as well.

title: Very helpful application
body: This has really helped me while shopping! I've set things back down on the shelves after seeing how low they scored and purchased healthier products! Really a handy, helpful tool!! Love it! Have told several people about it and they are enjoying it too!

title: Best ever
body: This is not only my "go to app", I use this app so much I seldom log out.  My eating life style is to eat only natural unprocessed foods.  What an eye opener this app was!  When I shop I use the scanner and my list to make purchases. This prevents me from taking home a bad choice that I would end up eating later.

title: Love ShopWell!!
body: This app is so easy to use and so incredibly helpful!! I walk through the grocery store and if I'm unsure of a product, I scan it - no problems. The categories show me foods that are tailored for me so that I can look at my options. And it makes my grocery lists easy to find! Love it

title: Great app but with some limits
body: I love this app to help track down celiac friendly foods! However I also have several other food allergies that aren't an option for avoidance. My biggest complaint (and the reason for the 4 star rating instead of 5) is the lack of option to avoid meat and animal products for vegetarian/vegan diets.

title: Life saver
body: I was recently diagnosed with celiac disease at the age of 42. My whole life I was fine! So its been a complete diet change for myself and my wife as well.  To make it short,......

title: Instant Food Knowledge
body: Not only am I learning more about the food in my cupboard but I'm having fun doing it. I scan everything. It's awesome. Food I thought was good I'm finding out is not and I've already used it to bring home an entirely new shopping bag list. Highly recommend this app.

title: Awesome!
