body: Two stars for the idea!  Unfortunately it only recognized 2 out of the 10 items I scanned, and 0 of 10 Trader Joe's products.

title: Awesome
body: This is a great app!  I just walked out of Earth Fare and this app made shopping so easy. I am putting my autistic son on a GF/CF diet and am a little intimidated. Lots of options on this app from typing in the product name you want info on to scanning barcodes for nutrition info. And it takes into consideration the parameters you set for allergies.

title: Pretty neat
body: I love the concept of this app. The only thing I could see improvements on for now is creating a larger database for the bar codes this app can recognize. For example, I scanned something from Trader Joes and the scanner didn't recognize it. Mac and cheese to be exact. Other than that the app runs great and has cool features. Keep up the good work

title: Outstanding
body: I've used several apps for fitness & diet tracking - this is, by far, one of the easiest & most user friendly. Other apps became a pain to track but this one is so easy, I actually want to track my exercise and intake. Well worth getting üëçüèª

title: Super Helpful and Easy!
body: Definitely a recommended app!!! Scanning products I already use is amazing and gives tons of info about the product. Being able to save items to a grocery list and send to a friend is extremely useful if he/she is shopping for me. LOVE IT! :))

title: New favorite app!
body: Our family loves this app!  The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is because of inaccuracies.  It seems to pick up "manufactured in a facility with ... (Soy etc.." as an actual ingredient in the product.   Otherwise, very very helpful, especially for someone new to reading labels.  Very impressed with the quantity of products in the database.

title: Pretty cool
body: I just got it and went through my pantry, but  a lot of the things they weren't in the data base. I also shop a lot at Costco, and the scanning option didn't pick up the "in bulk" selections. After I entered them in the search part I found some of them though. I was really looking forward to the scan part for the ease though. All in all,  pretty cool otherwise.

title: Helpful!
body: We recently found out my husband may have a gluten intolerance. The scan feature was very helpful on our first trip to the grocery store after we heard the news.

title: So far so good
body: The app is very user friendly and very useful. I hope to see the app add an avoidance for "nightshades" as those foods have been known to cause inflammation especially if you have existing skin conditions. All in all a great app and I look forward to the updates that come out. Thanks!

title: Frustrated
body: I loved this app when I first got it.   I used it all the time.  Since I've updated it I can no longer use it.   I've tried to set up a login account an it won't go beyond the screen that ask if I'm male or female the number of people I shop for and my age.   Not sure why that I for is important.  As of now I consider this app worthless and wouldn't recommend it until it's made more user friendly.  I don't have time to stand in the store and input info in order check the label.

title: Thorough, Accurate, Easy with Scanner
body: I have found this app to be the most accurate, have the most products listed and is very easy! You can scan an item rather than search. It also has the most filters for the most ailments. So awesome!!!

title: Awesome!!!
body: This app has helped me so much with going gluten free due to celiac. Great for healthy options/alternatives for anyone trying to eat better. I have suggested this app to all of my Facebook friends and patients who think purchasing healthy foods take too long due to reading all the ingredients.

title: Awesome App Helps You Shop Right!
body: I love this app... Enter your health goals and then scan everything you  buy or have in your cabinets. If its nit a good match, the app will tell you why and suggest better foods. Wish it had some sort pf shopping list feature, but it is a great app!! Syncs with Health Kit!

title: Very helpful
body: Being recently gluten free this app has helped with checking food products out. Though not everything is on the app the ability to take a photo and send in the team not found is a plus.

title: To be seen
body: I absolutely love this app I use it every time I go shopping. However I gave this app 1 star so hopefully this comment will be seen. Most of the time while shopping I try to be reasonable and look at both store brand and non-name brand items. I was a little disappointed to see that the brand Kroger was nowhere to be found on this app along with grocery stores just as King Soopers brand. I hope to see these brands and many more soon. And when it happens I will definitely give the app five stars.

title: Love it, just one recommendation
body: I love this, the scan feature and the way the app gives healthier alternatives is awesome!  My only wish is that I could use this for all items (like dog food, hygiene products etc...). Add that and this would be a 5 star app, even without that I still love this app and highly recommend to all my friends!

title: Really helpful
body: I like that I can scan what we already buy and it gives me healthy alternatives. I thought the healthy alternative would be some brand I had never heard of but it is all pretty common. It even tells me what stores nearby I can find things at.

title: Eh
body: I really want to like this app but I can't get fully behind it. I'm a healthy eating person and the products I scan are rarely in this app. I shop at Trader Joe's and have yet to find one of their products in here. I rarely find products in here from the health food section of major grocery stores either. I would appreciate this app much more if it had more products in it.

title: Gluten Free finder
body: Our 13 year old son was recently diagnosed with Celiac and this app helps out so much at the stores! We read the labels and then to make certain we scan! Needs a little update as some foods are now in fact GF and the app still states otherwise. A must have for Celiacs!!

title: So so
body: I liked the app at the beginning, but lately I've noticed some changes: the main change is that this app on healthy cereals gives 64 out of 100, and suggests Safeway or total and gives them 100. But when I look at the ingredients , their consistency is worse. So I wonder if the app gets paid by bigger companies like Kellogg , Total and etc . I'm looking for another app.

title: Love this app!
body: If you really want to know what you're putting in your mouth or you have food sensitivities and allergies this app is for you! It's really easy to use and it's really informative. I only wish that the suggested foods included other grocery stores besides Target and Walmart

title: Easy to use but many mistakes
body: As recently diagnosed with celiac, I wanted an easy to use app to scan foods to see if they are safe.  For the most part this app does the job.  However, I'm finding more and more products labeled as gluten free being flagged as not safe due to wheat.  One of the products was being flagged because in the ingredients it said "Produced in a dedicated facility free from: gluten, wheat, dairy, peanuts, tree nuts and sesame."

title: Dad
body: I have celiac disease so this is a must. My only complaint is occasionally it says an item I scan says it's OK even though it has wheat as an Ingredient. I have to go in and update my List of items I cannot eat(wheat/gluten). And then it works again. Not sure why it does this.

title: Easy and quick
body: Great while walking through the grocery store trying to decide on products that are healthy. Plus it gives you suggestions of better items right away.

title: Just great!
body: Honestly may save my life. I never know what to buy when I go to the store. I just grab whatever interests me or is on sale but now I have a list of items that I know are going to be healthier and not just what I think is healthy because some commercial or advertisement told me so. Awesome!

title: Amazing app for newbies to the health food craze
body: This app has really helped me turn around the way I shop. I love how it lets you highlight the things you specifically want to see increased or decreased in your diet. Not only has it helped me though, it has changed what I feed my entire family.

title: Has some weaknesses, but not bad
body: Doesn't have an option for no sugar, or low/no carbs. But I'm still trying to learn the app. Adding low-glycemic foods would be a huge plus.

title: Great app :)
body: I think that this is a really great app! I do like some features I have seen others mention, like more items, or to show us what local stores would have some of this! Another thing I wish it would add is the option to have Low Carb as well!

title: Think you're buying healthy?.....
body: This is such an awesome app!!!!!

title: A Must Have!!
body: I love this app!! So very helpful. However, I would love to see, in my 'allergies/foods to avoid,' a meat option for the vegetarians. Also, a clean eating option would make this app even better! Overall... A must have!! (If you care about what you put into your body!!)

title: GREAT APP!
body: Finally an app that helps make it easier to find out what items have gluten in it. As one that has celiac disease, it's been taking me longer to shop since I have to read all ingredients. With this app, it makes it a whole lot easier! Thank you!!!

title: Love this app
body: This app is a must-have if you are celiac or gluten-intolerant. I use it multiple times a week for my gluten intolerance. I even have relatives using it now and they find it helpful for preparing meals that are safe for me to eat. A little slow to start sometimes, but great app overall

title: Awesome
body: This is a great idea. I am so excited to use this app. It makes it a lot easier to make healthier choices. The only thing is there are a lot of brands I've never heard of here on the West Coast. *** Maybe an option to select state or region/location so the database would include region specific Brands &/or Stores. **** not sure if that's asking too much. ;-/

title: Useless
body: I downloaded this to help me as I was starting my gluten free diet to treat my severe migraines. Everything I scanned was a bad match, even foods that I ended up looking up on my own that were completely safe with absolutely no gluten. The other foods it didn't have in its database, which were common, brand name foods. It either gave me the wrong answer or no answer at all. I would not recommend this app to anyone. It was a waste of time to me when I really needed help during such a drastic lifestyle change.

title: Best. App. Ever.
body: I normally don't write reviews, but this app definitely garners support. I have a food allergy, and this app has helped save me from having a reaction on a few occasions. It also recommends foods that are better aligned with my fitness goals. Scanning products are my new favorite obsession. Thank you ShopWell on a great app!

title: No thinking
body: I'd recommend this if you don't want to have to think every time you shop. Trustworthy app tells you if it's healthy/has an allergen in it. Very convenient for a person who is busy and trying to stay healthy. Takes the guesswork out of shoppin.

title: Amazing App!!!!
body: This App is extremely helpful and I found it awesome that the store brand rices and noodles are better quality nutritionally than the name brand stuff...and cheaper!! This is a must have for those of you trying to get fit and eat right...this is the tool to eating right...no excuses now!

title: Good, but limited
body: Works well but limited to common wants, allergies, and avoidances.

title: Awesome app
body: Just started using this app today. So far, it seems really user friendly and easy to figure out. I love that I can make a grocery list ON this app instead of having to switch between different apps. Great! I highly recommend.

title: I love this app!
body: I love that you can get specific on your dietary concerns in your settings. I wish that you could be a little more specific in the allergies section, but overall it is still pretty good. I use it every time I go shopping & had my fianc√© download it!

title: Tons of food allergies in our house!
body: This app makes it so much easier to understand the contents in food. All of the monodioxpoly whatever's are translated into actual foods. There's so many hidden allergens in those big words that were making us wind up in the Er or Dr.'s weekly.

title: Incredibly useful
body: I am corn intolerant and this app is awesome. Saves me so much time checking every single ingredient! Only complaint is that it doesn't have a lot of brands, but when they have it it works very well.

title: Way Better than Expected!
body: It lets you choose what you want and don't want in your products and gives you multiple options and reasons why a certain product would or wouldn't be good for you. So great!

title: The most used APP for grocery shopping!!
body: I have Celiac Disease and ShopWell has made my grocery shopping less hectic!! I love trying new foods so this app has saved me. It also suggests other alternative product with scores if I have to avoid an ingredient in a product I was scanning. Love it!!

title: Pretty great, needs a few things.
body: I love it but it tends to steer you toward more expensive name brands when which is not for you if you are on a tight budget. Also can't read generic brands. Also there should be an option that it only gives you alternatives that are exactly what you are scanning. For example, if I'm scanning tuna, I want tuna. Not salmon.

title: Great!
body: This is a great app to see what foods would be beat for your conditions. You give then your allergies, goals, and what is important in your diet and they find foods that can help you achieve your goals. You can look up all types of food and then add them to a grocery list.

title: I'd be lost without it.
body: Test results say my body hates gluten - I was super bummed that I'd have to breakup with all the delicious gluten-containing foods I once loved, but this app made me optimistic of everything thing I can still enjoy. I could scan and browse foods all day!

title: It crashes all the time
body: It seems workers of this company post the reviews all the time  but the truth is that it doesn't work.

title: Flawless
body: I never usually write reviews for my food apps but this time around I had to! Organized, sleek design, liable, and extremely functional for whatever your needs are. The food scanner will become your fairy-godmother. Must-have app if you are health conscious!

title: I really like this app!
body: I really like this app. I was recently put on a very restrictive diet for health reasons and this app is proving to be very very helpful. The scan item makes it so much easier to find the nutritional data when the item doesn't have a good list.

title: Best app ever!!!
body: My sister showed me this app because well I'm not the best when it comes to food, but this app is soo great and really helpful.! Super addictive too, as soon as I got it I was scanning everything in my house it really does work and it's a great way to manage your food :)

title: Great app!!!
body: I was very excited to stumble upon this app!  Since changing my daughter over to a gluten free diet, reading each and every label at the grocery store before putting the product in my cart was such a tedious task.  This app has saved me a lot of frustration and time!  Thank you!!

title: Best nutrition app
body: Not only does the app explain why a product is or is not a good fit for for me based upon my own health goals, it advises me of better options. If I'm in a store when I scan the UPC, it first searches for trade-up options available in that store. It's so intelligent!

title: What an amazing tool!!!
body: This has come in handy since finding out I have celiac disease. So many products that I thought were ok turned out to be not so much. This is helping me figure out what foods I can have and what might be better choices for me! I'm loving this app!!!

title: Trumps Fooducate
body: This is way better than fooducate because it is customizable to goals and provides real details about foods.

title: Ahh-maze-ZING!!
body: This was so helpful. I couldn't figure out why I run 5 miles and do an hr of intense cardio workouts while watching what I eat but still pack on the pounds. This helped me watch for gluten and lactose which highly effect my body since I can't process them well. This +lose it. App = results!

title: Good app üëç
body: Nice looking app and pretty useful in terms of helping me find healthier food options. I was trying to compare various brands of chocolate milk (my trainer üí™ says it's a good workout recovery drink) the other day and I was able to find a brand that's better than the one I bought.

title: Life saver and beautifully designed
body: This app is amazing in every way. I recently found out I'm allergic to wheat and this app makes it so much easier to  avoid wheat while shopping. It's also gotten me to eat healthier and the interface is very well designed.

title: Tostitos
body: When I used your app to scan Tostito's Restaurant Style chips it told me I could not have them because of soy. It was not listed on the back of the bag so I called Frito Lay. Frito Lay said that as of May they have pulled all soybean out of these chips. Just wanted to let you know!  Otherwise this app is great!

title: Great app
body: Awesome app, I was just diagnosed with celiac disease, and this app is so helpful. I don't have to worry about googling products to double check them for safety, I can just scan them here and it does it for me. Plus I can modify it, not only for gluten free products, but also high and sugar and such.

title: Impressed
body: I just got this app so I really can not give it all 5 stars just yet! But I played around with it and I'm amazed to see what this app can do for me when I shop for my diabetic husband or for myself when I'm shopping for certain foods for my challenges. This app is going to be my #1 app when shopping!

title: Awesome app.
body: This is exactly the app I have been looking for. It works great. I just wish it had a low carb feature as well.

title: BEST APP
body: This app is a lifesaver! I am so thankful for this database, it makes it so easy to avoid all of my allergens and also see facts about my health goals when grocery shopping!! Thank you for creating this app, it is honestly life changing!!!! :)

title: Love this app!!!
body: Very helpful for anyone trying to eat right or has eating restrictions. You can also have your whole family logged in to your profile so you can shop for their eating restrictions as well! Love it and easy to use!!!

title: Unreliable for gluten free foods
body: If you must avoid wheat gluten, it's all or nothing. So what am I supposed to think of a product rating that is less than a 100 percent match for the search term "gluten" and a sole profile of "gluten-free"? A product either has gluten (NOT acceptable in ANY quantity for those with celiac disease) or it does not. Expensive processed packaged "health" foods dominate the lists. We don't all live in sophisticated cities where grocery stores have aisles and aisles of this stuff. In summary, app is useless if you need to avoid wheat gluten.

title: Spot hidden transfats with Shopwell and awesome shopping list!
body: Love to use this app to learn about foods and nutrition and to make my list.  What's really cool is the app actually spotted trams fats in a food I was considering.  I didn't realize that even if the label says 0% trams fats it is not always true.  Great app for grocery shopping.

title: What about Carbohydrates?
body: One of my biggest focuses as an athlete is juggling my macronutrient I take through the seasons. Right now, my main focus is cutting carbs and upping my protein and healthy fats... With that said, why doesn't this app allow the user to select "High Carbohydrates" as a flag to set for foods? It seems like everything else is perfectly fine but I find this missing feature bothersome.

title: Love this app!!!
body: I use this when I go shopping now. If I'm not sure if a product is healthy or a good choice, I scan the barcode and the app does the work for me! I was surprised to see some things aren't as a good choice as I might have though, while others being better than expected!

title: The best app ever....
body: This app is amazing!! I can take care of what i eat so much easier this way!!Better than reading the nutrition on everything. I just enter what i need and not need for my body , then scan the package and it tells me exactly what's good for me and what's bad.

title: Scanner needs expansion
body: Nothing I scan is in the database. This is a great app, and it makes creating a shopping list easy. Now, if it had more items to scan (nothing at Trader Joes shows up) and it found the nearest store with the food in your shopping list, it would be top notch!

title: Awesome but lacking a feature
body: I absolutely love this and would have rated it a 5 if it could include "pork by products" or gelatin as an allergen or good ingredient listing.  Also, another great feature would be to add KOSHER/HALAL seal of approval.  That'll really cut my search.  On top of that, is to add alcohol listing thread in the search factor.

title: Love the app
body: I love this app, scans food fast. I wish you would add more foods and also vitamins and supplements. I found the app while searching for gluten free apps. It has helped me a lot to make sure I'm not eating gluten. And it gives alternative foods that are healthier options

title: Food allergies
body: Love this app. My grandson's girlfriend has serious food allergies. It has made buying food for her much easier. We always read labels, but it's nice to have a back up. We have food a couple foods that were not labeled with nuts but came up in the app.

title: Superb - Can't believe this is Free
body: I'm lactose intolerant and his app has saved my from a lot of what could have been bad experiences. I would not have guessed that some foods contained lactose. I find myself scanning it searching everything I have just for fun and to be safe. Great app!

title: Love it!!!
body: Just downloaded app started scanning things in my fridge and oh my!!! It's simple to use and fast... Love how you can customize your target Area like eating healthy weight management diabetes high blood pressure...what you want to cut out or minimize like added sugar high fructose...thanks for this app :)

title: Amazing App!
body: I really love this app! I've been exercising and eating healthier over the past year, and I can already tell that this app is really helping! Especially sonde it gives me healthier alternatives! Definitely a must for anyone trying to improve their diet or lose weight!

title: This app is amazing!!
body: I been on diet after diet, but it doesn't help if you don't know what foods are better and not so better for you specifically. This app helps you understand food labels so you can choose what is best for you and see what is not!

title: Awesome and easy
body: I was just diagnosed with Celiac Disease and this app has made my life a lot easier to detect whether I not I can have certain foods :) gluten is in so many things I would have never thought it would be and now I know thanks to the app

title: Love
body: Makes grocery shopping a whole lot easier when you are trying to watch what you eat, and are trying to make healthier decisions. I love that it gives alternatives to other things, also!

title: Shop well
body: I love this app. Not being able to have gluten really messes me up. So who want to sit in a store and read the food labels? This app is great for that and I love the missions. I only have this 4 stars because every time I go out of this app it logs me out. If the was not a problem it would be 5 stars.

title: Gave wrong information
body: I was excited when I found this app, but then the very first product that I scanned (vanilla coke) came up saying that it contained gluten, I found this strange, because previous research told me that it did not, so I contacted the company to find out that it in fact does not contain gluten. I guess there is no point in using this app if it is going to give me the wrong. Information on such an important allergy, who knows what other foods it will get wrong?

title: Tremendously helpful!!
body: My son is allergic to foods that are not required to be individually listed on food labels.  This app sometimes is the only way I know if sesame is present. Most foods are in the database but some off brands are not.

title: Helpful App
body: You sometimes don't even know what you're buying these days in the supermarket. This app not only rates the products you scan but gives you better suggestions to buy. Love it!

title: Great app but freezes
body: This is the best when it comes to finding what's not good for you based on your specifications. It even tells you what other options are better for you based on your specifications. It freezes up shop that's the only downfall.

title: Makes life so much easier
body: I love this app! Makes shopping easier. I am over weight and was looking for something to help with my food choices. Thanks to this app I can do this now. I have lost 10lbs so far. I highly recommend.

title: Great but...
body: I like this because its clear and helps you easily find foods you can or cannot eat! and its customizable to your dietary needs.

title: Very disappointing.
body: I agree with the users that complained about the lack of products in the app's database. Out of the 60 items in my kitchen that I scanned, the app only recognized the Kikkoman soy sauce! It didn't even recognize something as common as Quaker oats or Heinz ketchup!

title: Best app
body: This has been so helpful. I have celiac disease and find reading labels to be a long task. I pull my phone out scan the product and it tells me if I can have that item or not. It's made shopping so much faster and easier

title: Impressed!
body: Amazing app! Really gets specific for your meal type. Even tells the location of the items, which is a great help. Without this app I wouldn't know how healthy some items are! :) Definitely worth downloading.

title: Amazing!!
body: This is the best app ever! It really helps you acknowledge what's in the food you're eating and it helps you to stay on track in you're healthy lifestyle. This app takes the food you eat and finds you a healthier option, it's great.

title: Easy To Use!
body: Download & Try it & you'll love it.

title: Great App
body: This is a must have app when going to the grocery. I've been very surprised at what I thought was good for me turn out not so good and was able to select better options from their suggestions.

title: Love the idea
body: I love how easy it is to scan an item to see if I can eat it, and if not, they suggest something else I can. However, I wish I could pick out specific items since I can't eat chocolate or certain fruit, so it doesn't help if the recommendations include them.

title: Get it if you want to turn your phone into a snob that judges you
body: It automatically assumes I care about a tiny amount of added sugar and that I'd literally rather have everything be organic.  I set it to only check for gluten and it is telling me that spaghetti sauce is a medium match for me only based on sodium and it doesn't say anything about gluten and then suggests other stuff that is way worse in other aspects like fat and saturated fat.  Go for it if you're a cuckolded hipster.

title: This App is incredible! I can't shop without it.

title: Amazing app

title: Almost perfect
body: Everything about is almost except for one thing. The location services should also be used to show where are the nearest places to get the healthy foods or where we can order them online if possible.

title: Wow

title: Great idea but...
body: As I absolutely love this app. However I find it useless and I'm grateful that I didn't pay for it. 96% of everything that I look up is not in the database. If you simply buy really mass-produced goods, basic brands that you find at you're mainstream grocery stores this is a good application, but if you shop at Whole Foods, healthier places, use healthier brands, or organic this would not work for you. Which is too bad I liked everything else about it.

title: Just what I was looking for.
body: As a celiac with lactose intolerance I've been very frustrated with trying to read ingredients. I was actually going to have my husband try & write an app to do pretty much what shop well does. I'm so excited. Thank you shopwell!

title: Great App
body: I use this app all the time when I go grocery shopping. I think the barcode scanner is a nice feature, as well as the rating system for my personal food and nutrition preferences. Highly recommended.

title: Perfect! I love this app
body: Excellent app. Provides really useful information, extremely easy to use, sleek design. I love it!

title: Love It!!
body: I have been looking for an app that just tells me exactly what my food has and if it's good for me. You can adjust it to your needs. Perfect! I didn't want all that extra stuff that other apps make you do.

title: Make it even better
body: Makes this app even better by giving more options to meet a wider range of dietary needs for folks like myself who are undergoing gastric bypass and all that am going to keep using it!

title: Overall awesome

title: Love it!
body: I recently found out I can't eat gluten, and at first I didn't know what I could or couldn't eat. Not only does it tell me if something is safe to eat, but it highlights exactly the ingredients I have to stay away from!

title: Great idea with some kinks!
body: This app is an awesome idea and will work great as soon as they iron out the kinks. Such as labeling (vegan) Daiya Cheese as having dairy and peanuts because in the ingredient list it says, "made in a dairy and peanut free facility". All in all this is a really helpful app and I will continue to use it and hope they correct these little things.

title: Makes Gluten Free shopping quicker

title: Good app for eliminating bad ingredients.
body: Overall great app! Brand variety is good. Some things I've never seen before in my local grocery. Having a gluten sensitivity I look for foods that are not high in starches that carry low nutrients. That would be a nice option to add to things to limit or avoid.

title: Lifesaver!
body: I downloaded this app as soon as I found out that I was gluten intolerant and allergic to eggs. This app has been a lifesaver in the grocery store making it easy to shop. I highly recommend it to anybody with allergies or food intolerance.

title: Valuable tool for vegetarians and vegans!!
body: Get this app!! It's amazing! No matter what you health goal (even diabetics) input the food and it will tell you why or why not you should eat it. I have been looking for an app like this and am sooo happy I found it!! And it's free! üòÉ

title: Great but not working with ios9
body: I was recently put on a low fodmap/gluten free diet and really need to use this app (I haven't used it in months) but now that I've updated to ios9 I can't login with Facebook (the button doesn't work) and when I try to create a new account the input boxes disappear.

title: Best App!

title: Eh

It would be amazing if you could just select that your a vegetarian though. That way you aren't looking at every ingredient on every suggestion. If/when that becomes an option I will rate all 5 stars.

title: So Awesome!

title: The best FREE healthy food helper

title: Exactly what I've been looking for!

That's a first for me to see in an app. After using it for a while I'll update my rating later.

When scrolling through the categories I noticed sometimes the same food is listed many times in succession making it appear as though there are more foods than there are. Many of the brands I don't recognize.  Would be helpful if they said what region of the country this is currently geared towards. Great idea but needs work.

title: Great app

title: Love it!

title: Truck Driver/Ex-Athlete
body: Love this app!Really helps me with my NY's resolution to eat healthier especially due to my being on the road as much as I am.Big up's ShopWell!!!

title: A.Maze.Ing!
body: Everything's all in one place! I can search sideways upside-down and in reverse, and this app will point me in MY right direction!!

title: Does not deliver
body: I was careful to select my nutritional parameters and it completely ignored my preferences and recommended foods that did not fall within my guidelines. Disappointing. I really wanted to like this app.-----deleted

title: Great App
body: Shop well is an excellent aid for determining what products to buy relative to one's dietary needs & what products to stay away from. The bar code scan feature is highly valuable for decision making.

title: Fast and easy
body: I have Celiac disease and I'm lactose intolerant so this app is very helpful when reading labels. All I have to do is scan the bar code and it will tell me if it's a safe food or not.

title: Love it
body: Best app on here.finally a app that helps me to pick the right food.thank you

title: Bomb.diggitycom!!!
body: Just started using this bad boy today!!! And I love love love it!!! Amazing at detecting anything and EVERYTHING you don't want in your food.

title: Newbie
body: I'm fairly new to closely watching what I eat and this app has been so helpful! A few tweaks to better color code the ingredients and added allergens would make this a 5 star app!!

title: What a great app!
body: It sure makes it a lot easier to identify foods that contain gluten.  I love the bar code scanner feature, it takes all of the guesswork out of shopping for healthy foods.

title: Good
body: Love.  It.  Eat.  The.  Best.  Buy.   The.  Best.  Live.  Longer

title: Nice!
body: Love this app! It works and the scanner is fun! (:

title: More options in profile
body: Iam new to this app but anxious to use it. I am battling a tough cancer and i would like to see more options in the avoid category and maybe soon there will be skin care products etc. because theres so much hidden bad ingredients that feeds cancer. Just an idea that many ppl will surely use.thanks

title: Good APP
body: Will give 5 stars when I can delete scanned items without having to put them in my list first and then deleting them.Takes to much time to delete if you add to list and then have to delete.

title: Interesting
body: So, it makes grocery shopping take a little longer.  So, it seems a little inconsistent in the ratings it gives to some foods, and some of the alternate choices are completely alien to me.  Still, this app gives me the ability to scan nearly any item in the grocery store and quickly confirm or debunk the claims of the manufacturer.

title: Cool
body: Cool app tells u the details of food u can also get a iTunes card for downloading app redeem and use my bonus code lingtong

title: Amazed
body: Once I learned how to use this app and created my own personal choice list as in what I really wanted in the foods I ate, it became really easy to distinguish what was good and bad. I love how you can scan the bar code any where and receive all the info needed.

title: Great app
body: My only complaint is that the bar code scanner makes this loud piercing sound. Is there a way to turn it off?

title: Great First Impression!
body: Just got it and can't stop scanning! Love it so far. An actually USEFUL app for this mom that has a child with milk and wheat intolerances.
